elements.name: As an administrator I create and publish a post

steps.name: I click on element having css selector "a[href="#/posts/"]"
I click on element having css selector "a[href="#/editor/post/"]"

I enter "Test Post Kraken Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long" into input field having css selector "div.gh-koenig-editor-pane > textarea"

I enter "Hello World Kraken Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long" into input field having css selector "div.gh-koenig-editor-pane div[contenteditable=true]"
I click on element having css selector "div.gh-publishmenu"
I click on element having css selector "button.gh-publishmenu-button"
I click on element having css selector "header a[href^="#/posts/"]"
I click on element having css selector "div.gh-contentfilter-type"
I click on element having css selector "ul > li[data-option-index="2"]"
I should see text "Test Post Kraken Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long Long"
